<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="79e03ac1-fbc7-5965-a135-46965df18e48" activityNameId="f0ec56f8-7152-448c-a045-4b47f06e06fa" parentActivityId="e6821ed2-4239-5c34-bcd1-150444c3b9f3" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">combine harvesting</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The combine harvesting process starts with preliminary work at the farm, like attaching the adequate machine to the tractor.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">This activity ends with transfer back to farm and concluding work, like uncoupling the machine. The inventory includes transfer to field; field work (for a parcel of land of 1 ha surface); the diesel fuel consumption and the amount of agricultural machinery and of the shed, which has to be attributed to the harvesting by combined harvester. Also taken into consideration is the amount of emissions to the air from combustion and the emission to the soil from tyre abrasion during the work process. The overlapping during the field work is considered. The amount of harvested fodder is not taken into account. Not included are dust other than from combustion and noise. The grain production and straw treatment are not included.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the service of combine harverster over 1 ha of agricultural land. The harvester is assumed to be 8 metres wide.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">Dataset exchanges scaled from GLO parent dataset based on diesel consumption in Australia with other flows on capital infrastructure being kept the same as global process.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">This inventory has been developed as part of the AusAgLCI initiative funded by a partnership of Australian Research and Development Corporations (RIRDC, CRDC, GRDC, SRDC, HAL, MLA, DA, FWPA) and Research Agencies (CSIRO, USQ and Q DAFF), with technical support from Life Cycle Strategies. More detail on inventory development can be found in the 'AusAgLCI Methodology for developing Life Cycle Inventory' documents located at www.Auslci.alcas.asn.au. Energy use from WA farm energy calculator.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">Fuel consumption data have been derived from the Western Australia Farm Energy Calculator for broadacre crop.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="bbe2eb06-fac9-48bb-9610-f402b9d3f2d0">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">0161:Support activities for crop production</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="09b1a988-7d7e-11de-9ae2-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">AU</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Fuel consumption data have been derived from the Western Australia Farm Energy Calculator for havesting from global defaults.</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Fuel use is from current technology used in Australia</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2012-01-01" endDate="2023-01-01" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Model is based on data in 2010</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
